      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:31:7",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ إِنَّ عَلِيّاً ( عليه السلام ) كَانَ يَقُولُ إِنَّ الرَّجُلَ إِذَا شَرِبَ الْخَمْرَ سَكِرَ وَ إِذَا سَكِرَ هَذَى وَ إِذَا هَذَى افْتَرَى فَاجْلِدُوهُ حَدَّ الْمُفْتَرِي ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Muhammad Bin Isa, from Yunus, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Ali<sup>asws</sup> was saying that the man, when he drinks the wine, gets intoxicated, and when he is intoxicated, raves, and when he raves, he fabricates, therefore he would be whipped a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) of the fabricator’."
        ]
      }
    }
